The incumbent chairman of AbajiÂ Area Council, Alhaji Abdulrahman Ajiya of the All Progressives Congress, APC, has been declared winner of the area council election. Alhaji Ajiya won with a margin of 2, 973 votes. The area council returning officer, Prof Simon Malankwe, who announced the result, said Ajiya won after he polled a total votes of 13, 442 to defeat his main opponent Alhaji Mohammed Inuwa Ashafa of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), who polled 10, 473 votes. FCT poll:  APC, PDP pick chairmanship candidates FCT poll:  APC, PDP pick chairmanship candidates FCT poll: APC wins Abaji, Bwari